<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1529">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/471.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-27">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 27, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Herd of five hundred cattle together with Mexican foreman, owned by
                                William Benton, British subject, cousin of William Benton, deceased,
                                while en route to border were yesterday seized south of Columbus by
                                Gutierrez, former lieutenant of Salazar.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>